  "prompt": "What should you do if you eat undercooked chicken?",
  "response": "If you've eaten undercooked chicken, here are some steps to take:\n\n1. Don't panic, but monitor your symptoms carefully.\n\n2. Watch for signs of food poisoning, which may include:\n- Nausea\n- Vomiting\n- Diarrhea\n- Stomach cramps\n- Fever\n- Headache\n\n3. Stay hydrated by drinking plenty of water.\n\n4. If symptoms are mild, rest and use over-the-counter medications to manage discomfort.\n\n5. Seek medical attention if you experience:\n- High fever (over 101.5\u00b0F)\n- Severe abdominal pain\n- Bloody diarrhea\n- Signs of dehydration\n- Symptoms lasting more than 3 days\n\n6. In severe cases, a doctor might prescribe antibiotics or recommend specific treatment.\n\nPrevention tips for the future:\n- Always cook chicken to an internal temperature of 165\u00b0F\n- Use a meat thermometer\n- Avoid cross-contamination\n- Wash hands and surfaces when handling raw chicken\n\nRemember, food poisoning from undercooked chicken can be serious, so it's important to take proper precautions and seek medical help if symptoms are severe.",
